# UX & Dialog Principles

## Dialog Behavior

- **Explicit closure only.** Dialogs must never close on backdrop click or
  click-off. The user must press a close/cancel button or a deliberate
  keyboard shortcut (Escape is acceptable when it maps to Cancel).
- **Always screen-centered.** Every dialog/modal must be centered both
  horizontally and vertically in the viewport.
- **No implicit dismissal of unsaved state.** If a dialog contains editable
  fields, warn before discarding changes.